TRADITIONAL PARTITIONING:              LIQUID CLUSTERING:
(folder-based, rigid)                  (file-level, flexible)

/table/date=2026-01-01/                /table/
  ├── part-001.parquet (1MB)  SMALL!     ├── file-001.parquet (1GB)
  ├── part-002.parquet (2MB)  SMALL!     │   (clustered by customer_id,
/table/date=2026-01-02/                  │    region - data sorted
  ├── part-001.parquet (1MB)  SMALL!     │    within files)
  ├── ...                                ├── file-002.parquet (1GB)
/table/date=2026-01-03/                  ├── file-003.parquet (1GB)
  ├── ...                                └── ...
  
10,000 partitions                      Data is CLUSTERED not PARTITIONED
= 10,000+ small files                 Optimally sized files (~1GB)
-- Enable Liquid Clustering (new table)
CREATE TABLE my_table (...)
CLUSTER BY (customer_id, region);

-- Change clustering keys (NO table rewrite!)
ALTER TABLE my_table CLUSTER BY (region, product_id);

-- Incrementally apply clustering
